<HEADLINE>
BUSINESS MERGER CASES DOUBLED IN 2006: ECONOMICS MINISTRY
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Taipei,  March 25 (CNA) 03/25/07  17:27:41 (By Deborah Kuo)
</P>
<P>
The number of business mergers completed in Taiwan in 2006
doubled to 203 from the level of a year-earlier with the value of
businesses involved totaling NT$126.5 billion (US$3.83 billion) ,
Ministry of Economic Affairs (MOEA) officials reported Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The number of business mergers has reached 736 cases, worth
NT$342.41 billion since the law governing business mergers was
put into force in 2002, MOEA official said.
</P>
<P>
By scale, the officials said, 58.1 percent, or 118 cases out of
the 203 merger cases completed in 2006 involved companies with
founding capital of NT$500 million or less.
</P>
<P>
Another 38 merger cases, or 18.7 percent, involved companies with
founding capital of NT$2 billion or more, the officials said.
</P>
<P>
By business type, they continued, electronic companies topped the
2006 business merger list, with 36 cases, which constituted 17.7
percent of the yearly record, followed by electrical engineering
companies (9.3 percent) , telecommunications companies (9.3
percent) and chemical companies (7.4 percent).
</P>
